{"name":"Arcane Affinity","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Some wizards choose to specialize in a particular kind of magic. They may be necromancers who study the lore of un-dead or pyromancers who control fire. They may be elementalists who can control free-willed elementals or summoners who bring material objects into existence from nowhere. These specialist mages go beyond the capabilities of normal magic-users by studying, pondering, and ultimately completely connecting to the school of arcane magic they choose. A necromancer may live with un-dead</p>\n<p>creatures to fully understand them. A pyromancer may dwell in a volcano. An elementalist may live on one of the four elemental planes, and a conjurer may study the atomic building blocks of matter.</p>\n<p>This spell is the mechanism by which specialty magic happens. This spell forms an affinity between the caster and one kind of magic. This affinity comes after much time and labor is expended and has a cost:</p>\n<p>the spell slot is forever occupied by this very spell, and the caster is forever connected to the arcane element he chooses. However, this spell also has a benefit: it makes the caster more powerful in a specific school of magic.</p>\n<p>Although this spell is listed in the caster&rsquo;s spellbook as the spell arcane affinity, it is really a different spell depending on each caster&rsquo;s goal. It truly represents the time and effort necessary to develop an affinity for a particular school of magic. The &ldquo;casting time&rdquo; is a set of rituals and actions necessary to form the affinity. This is a level 2 spell because a caster must understand the basic principles of magic before he can build an affinity. Traditional affinities and their &ldquo;casting time&rdquo; are as follows. Note the &ldquo;casting time&rdquo; can, in game terms, be considered to overlap with adventuring time or be a lull between adventures.</p>\n<p>&bull; Illusionist: A specialist in spells that alter perceptions or create false images and sounds. An illusionist must spend at least one year understanding how the human body processes sensory input and how it can be fooled.</p>\n<p>&bull; Summoner: A specialist in spells that summon animals, monsters, and other creatures to aid the caster, including elementals and demons. A summoner may further specialize in a particular kind of creatures summoned (e.g., elementals). Summoners may also specialize in summoning objects as well as creatures. A summoner must spend at least one year studying the creatures he wants to summon, both in captivity and in their natural surroundings.</p>\n<p>&bull; Necromancer: A specialist in the un-dead, their creation, their control, and their limits. A necromancer may ultimately pursue eternal life via his own transformation into an un-dead. A necromancer must spend at least one year in the presence of un-dead.</p>\n<p>&bull; Transmuter: A specialist in changing matter from one form to another, whether it be flesh to stone, iron to gold, or something in between. A transmuter must spend at least one year in a laboratory studying the properties of different materials.</p>\n<p>&bull; Pyromancer: A specialist in the study of fire. Pyromancers must spend at least one year in the presence of great flames, such as an active volcano or on the plane of fire. Pyromancers ultimately learn to create, control, and destroy flames at will. There are other specialists who study similar magical powers but control other elements; e.g., fulminators who study electricity, cryomancers who study cold, and aerialists who study air.</p>\n<p>&bull; Demonologist: A specialist in the summoning, control, exorcism, destruction, and lore of demons. This is a dangerous specialty, for demons are never willing to divulge the information necessary to control them. A demonologist must spend at least three years studying ancient tomes, consulting supernatural spirits, and traveling to distant planes to learn what he needs to control demons.</p>\n<p>After a specialist has committed the necessary &ldquo;casting time&rdquo; to specialize in one field, a spell check is made. The spell check determines the benefit of specialization, as noted below. Many specialists utilize spellburn at this point to ensure a good result. Some specialists may attempt ritualized versions of this spell by casting it in a place of power, in concert with other mages, or with an appropriate sacrifice. The ritual rules at the beginning of this chapter, combined with the judge&rsquo;s discretion, determine the nature of the ritual.</p>\n<p>The caster may choose to specialize in more than one field, provided he obeys the dictates given here and in the spell results. Because specialization typically results in improved spellcasting in certain spells and reduced spellcasting in others, a wizard with multiple specialties may find they begin to offset each other.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Arcane Affinity]{Arcane Affinity}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Self","duration":"Varies","page":"162","castingTime":"Varies","results":{"table":"Arcane Affinity","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/abstract-085.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3FyTDf2l0HD8UP5v"}
{"name":"Scare","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell causes its victim to experience abject terror, potentially fleeing the scene or cowering in fright.</p>\n<p>The spell does not affect automatons, golems, mindless un-dead (such as zombies or skeletons), and other creatures that do not feel fear.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Scare]{Scare}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"30' or more","duration":"1 round or longer","page":"191","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Scare","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will save vs. spell check DC","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/surprised-skull.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4e41QvyqwVSNlLLe"}
{"name":"Knock","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster forces open a locked portal or object.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Knock]{Knock}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"30' or more","duration":"Permanent","page":"175","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Knock","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/door-ring-handle.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5FOUQU1lNY5flNJO"}
{"name":"Forget","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster makes a creature forget something.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Forget]{Forget}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Touch or more","duration":"1 round or more","page":"170","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Forget","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/help.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6FsANXvNU6C1bWXW"}
{"name":"Locate Object","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell lets the caster locate an object. Weaker castings require a physical trace of the object, and it can only be located if it is on the same plane of existence. With more powerful castings, the caster can locate objects he has never beheld, even if they reside in a different plane or time.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Locate Object]{Locate Object}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Varies","duration":"1 round or 1 hour","page":"178","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Locate Object","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/magnifying-glass.svg","effects":[],"_id":"D59rxI1b2Qg86VLH"}
{"name":"Nythuul's Porcupine Coat","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell cloaks the caster in a bristling layer of sharp quills. The quills act as armor, increases unarmed melee damage, and with more potent results, can be used as a ranged weapon.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Nythuul's Porcupine Coat]{Nythuul's Porcupine Coat}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Self","duration":"1 round per CL","page":"186","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Nythuul's Porcupine Coat","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/troglodyte.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EDyVQyuT225U3ix7"}
{"name":"Detect Invisible","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster activates an inner sight to see the true nature of things. In doing so, he is able to see invisible creatures and objects. If the target creature or object is protected by an invisibility shield (per the invisibility spell), the caster&rsquo;s spell check counts as the DC for the target&rsquo;s Will save.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Detect Invisible]{Detect Invisible}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"60' or more","duration":"Varies","page":"165","castingTime":"1 Action","results":{"table":"Detect Invisible","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check DC","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/secret-door.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HHFeycAZBLyDLlXU"}
{"name":"Wizard Staff","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>With this spell, the wizard crafts a staff and imbues it with magical energies linked to his soul. A wizard can create only one staff at a time and suffers great pains if it is destroyed. The material cost is 1,000 gp per caster level, plus any unusual materials (e.g., an adamantine staff requires sufficient adamantine), plus a minimum of 2 points of spellburn per caster level to properly bond the staff. One point of this spellburn never heals; it is permanent ability loss. Additionally, the caster must have the requisite spells that will be placed into the staff, and be able to utilize them without rest during the casting period.</p>\n<p>The casting period is ongoing with brief spurts of restless sleep, and the caster does not heal spellburn (or other wounds) during this time. The staff&rsquo;s efficacy is much greater at higher caster levels, and thus the time and material cost rises as the wizard progresses in power level. In the descriptions below, &ldquo;original caster level&rdquo; refers to the level at which the wizard crafted the staff &ndash; if he advances in level after creating the staff, abilities associated with original caster level do not increase.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Wizard Staff]{Wizard Staff}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Self","duration":"Permanent","page":"199","castingTime":"1 week per caster level","results":{"table":"Wizard Staff","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/wizard-staff.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LTunKSrAFNnrG5cl"}
{"name":"ESP","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster can detect the thoughts of other creatures. Lower check results allow the caster to read only surface-level thoughts. With higher check results the caster can concentrate and read deeper levels of thought with each round of continuous concentration, as follows. Detecting the answer to a specific question within the scope of the thoughts described below generally takes [[/roll 1d4]] rounds once the appropriate round of concentration is reached. For example, finding out where an evil necromancer hid his magic ring takes [[/roll 1d4]] rounds after the 4th round of concentration (recent memories), and understanding why the necromancer bears an irrational hatred toward the king takes [[/roll 1d4]] rounds after the 6th round of concentration (subconscious motivations).</p>\n<p>Round 2: The caster understands any long-range goals and motivations associated with the creature&rsquo;s current thoughts and actions.</p>\n<p>Round 3: The caster understands the creature&rsquo;s relationships with its friends and enemies.</p>\n<p>Round 4: The caster can read the creature&rsquo;s recent memories. It still takes time to sort through all the</p>\n<p>thoughts &ndash; roughly one round for every day of memories.</p>\n<p>Round 5: The caster can read the creature&rsquo;s historical memories &ndash; as far back as it can remember.</p>\n<p>Round 6: The caster understands the creature&rsquo;s subconscious thoughts - motivations and underlying behaviors that it may not even be aware of.</p>\n<p>Certain higher check results allow the caster to switch targets. Switching to a new target triggers a new Will save for the new target, and resets the &ldquo;round counter&rdquo; for purposes of reading deep thoughts.</p>\n<p>For example, if the caster concentrated for three rounds on one target, then switched to a second, then switched back to the first, it would be as if he was starting back at one round of concentration.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.ESP]{ESP}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"100' or more","duration":"1 Round or more","page":"166","castingTime":"1 Round","results":{"table":"ESP","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check DC","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Mji5mJaD8cNviLu1"}
{"name":"Phantasm","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>With this spell, the caster creates a simple illusion. The illusion is strictly visual, with no aural, tactile, or olfactory components. With concentration, the caster can manipulate the illusion.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Phantasm]{Phantasm}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"100' or more","duration":"1 round or longer, with concentration","page":"187","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Phantasm","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check DC","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/haunting.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N4gVs6KVQmMmJTm1"}
{"name":"Levitate","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster or a target chosen by the caster levitates into the air. This spell is useful for getting over walls or into canyons and handy for carrying heavy objects.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Levitate]{Levitate}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Self or further (see below)","duration":"Varies","page":"176","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Levitate","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/floating-platforms.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OTSsyFtla4TWeec5"}
{"name":"Invisibility","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster makes himself invisible. This spell can also render allies invisible and can create an invisibility shield that prevents detection by other spells.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Invisibility]{Invisibility}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Self or more","duration":"Varies","page":"172","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Invisibility","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check DC (sometimes)","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/invisible.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VLJ8oB3H5xDpilAr"}
{"name":"Strength","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>With an arcane incantation, the caster grants physical strength to a willing target.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Strength]{Strength}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Varies","duration":"Varies","page":"198","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Strength","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/weight-lifting-up.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XYenzTkL8WuP2jar"}
{"name":"Shatter","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster shatters a physical object. This spell causes damage to inanimate objects and is particularly effective at objects made of crystal or glass. It has the potential to not only damage the object immediately but also cause ongoing fractures that make it more susceptible to future damage.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Shatter]{Shatter}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Touch or further","duration":"Instantaneous or longer","page":"193","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Shatter","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/shattered-sword.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YuJI0zZ3OBqLfcI8"}
{"_id":"c4FcO57TMsGpQAOV","name":"Detect Evil (Wizard Casting)","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The cleric holds up his holy symbol and detects emanations of evil within a ray that extends straight out 5&rsquo; wide and 60&rsquo; (or more) ahead of the symbol. The definition of &ldquo;evil&rdquo; is based on the cleric: generally it encompasses creatures of opposed alignment, those unholy to the cleric&rsquo;s deity, and those with clearly harmful intent. Depending on the strength of the spell, it may detect even more subtle dangers. This spell does not reveal creatures that are otherwise hidden but does inform the cleric that evil intentions radiate from a certain position. This spell may be reversed to detect good, which means creatures of allied alignment, common deity, or similar holy goals.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;This is the Wizard version of a Cleric spell as described in the footnote in @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.LxWvwON9h9JWpI6c]{Table 5-8: Wizard Spells}. The difficulty has been adjusted accordingly and a misfire added on a result of 1.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Detect Evil (Wizard Casting)]{Detect Evil (Wizard Casting)}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritActionDie":true,"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":1,"range":"60 radius from cleric or more (see below)","duration":"6 turns","page":"259","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Detect Evil (Wizard Casting)","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check DC (sometimes)","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/spyglass.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Spider Web","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster creates a sticky spider web with which to entangle his foes. Unless objects are trapped by the web, it is difficult to see, effectively invisible unless someone is searching for it. A creature that touches the web is held fast, able to escape only by a DC 20 Strength or Agility check. The web can be burned off (possibly wounding captured creatures) or hacked through with a very sharp blade by a creature not already caught (AC 16, 5 hp to free one creature). A dull blade or blunt object will simply become entangled; even a strike with an exceptionally sharp blade has a 25% chance of entangling the weapon. Melee attacks aimed at the creatures held by the web run a 10% risk per attack of entangling the attacker.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Spider Web]{Spider Web}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Varies","duration":"Varies","page":"196","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Spider Web","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Varies (see below)","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/spider-web.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ida1KmcpCAen4vv7"}
{"name":"Scorching Ray","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster summons the flames of Hell to immolate his foes.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Scorching Ray]{Scorching Ray}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"80'","duration":"Instantaneous","page":"192","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Scorching Ray","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Ref partial (see below)","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/fire-ray.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rEJNVu2Lqw3vkoh2"}
{"name":"Fire Resistance","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster increases his resistance to heat and fire.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Fire Resistance]{Fire Resistance}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"Self or more","duration":"1 turn or more","page":"169","castingTime":"1 round","results":{"table":"Fire Resistance","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"N/A","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/fire-shield.svg","effects":[],"_id":"s5NAFMH48N114xIh"}
{"name":"Monster Summoning","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The caster must spend half the casting time drawing pentacle, then the remaining casting time conjuring monster spirits. At end of the turn, the caster summons forth a monster. He must be familiar with the monster, and it must be native to this plane of existence. The master must have some material remnant of the monster to expend in the spell (e.g., hair, fur, paw, tooth, skull, etc.).</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Monster Summoning]{Monster Summoning}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"20'","duration":"Varies","page":"184","castingTime":"1 turn or less","results":{"table":"Monster Summoning","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"None","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/brute.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sIEmbliwiIV4n1om"}
{"name":"Ray of Enfeeblement","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This necromantic spell requires at least 1 point of spellburn. The caster issues a dangerous strength-draining ray, which destroys the physical prowess of a target. Reducing a creature to 0 Strength transforms it into a jelly-like mass, unable to support its own weight or defend itself from attacks. If a target does not have a defined Strength score, assume 10 for normal humans and man-sized creatures. Lost ability scores heal back at the normal rate.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Ray of Enfeeblement]{Ray of Enfeeblement}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":"","summary":""},"source":"","config":{"inheritSpellCheck":true},"available":true,"level":2,"range":"150'","duration":"Instantaneous","page":"190","castingTime":"1 action","results":{"table":"Ray of Enfeeblement","collection":"dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-tables-wizard"},"save":"Will vs. spell check","spellCheck":{"die":"1d20","value":0},"mercurialEffect":{"value":null,"summary":"","description":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/achilles-heel.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uP8925isf083D6R3"}
